honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl

Class PrinterData_ExPCL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.expcl.PrinterData_ExPCL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrinterState_ExPCL

    public abstract class PrinterData_ExPCL
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is the base class for the printer state code. This will handle configuration queries and settings and all of the shared routines for the sub-classes that each handle a specific printer query.

      • getValid

        public boolean getValid()
        This is true if the configuration information is valid. If the printer doesn't support the functionality or query failed this will return false.

        Because not all queries are valid for all printer configurations this parameter is designed to indicate if the PrinterState_ExPCL object is populated with any values. A false value can mean either the object has never had Update run, or that when an update was performed nothing was returned from the printer.

        Returns:
        If the configuration information is valid.

      • update

        public void update(java.lang.String responseString)
        This will parse the query response from the printer to update the values for this set of parameters. All current values will be replaced with the values on the printer.

        Initially the PrinterState_ExPCL objects are empty. Use this to update them with the latest values from the printer. Unlink the other version of Update which takes the connection object to the printer and handles the querying for you, this version takes the query response. This allows the querying to be done at another time than processing.

        Parameters:
        responseString - This is the string returned from the printer for this query.

      • queryResult

        public java.lang.String queryResult(java.lang.String name)
        This will return a string value of the parameter token specified. If the token is not present then null is returned.

        This function is good for generically accessing data of PrinterState_ExPCL objects.

        Parameters:
        name - Name of the parameter to retrieve the value for.
        Returns:
        String with the value of the parameter.

      • queryResults

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> queryResults()
        This will return an array list of the items returned in the query it the form of Name{tab}Value.

        This function is good for generically accessing data of PrinterState_ExPCL objects. Altering these values does on alter their actual value.

        Returns:
        ArrayList with the Name and Value items separated by a tab.
